 estimates of the human and economic costs of disasters triggered by natural hazards in 2021 across the Asia-Pacific region. 8 Delivering on the Sustainable Development Goals through Solutions at the Energy, Food and Finance Nexus Figure 6: Disasters triggered by natural hazards in Asia and the Pacific, 2021 Figure 7: Number of disasters in Asia and the Pacific, 2018-2022 Source:\ufffd EM-DAT\ufffdThe\ufffdinternational\ufffddisasters\ufffddatabase,\ufffd2021. Source:\ufffd EM-DAT\ufffdThe\ufffdinternational\ufffddisasters\ufffddatabase,\ufffd2021 DISASTERS DEATHS ECONOMIC DAMAGE ASIA PACIFIC 177 of which 75.7% are floods and storms 16 of which 93.7% are floods and storms 5,041 of which 62% are from floods of which 73% 15 are from storms $52.4B $3.6B Across subregions, South-East Asia has experienced the most disasters since 2019, followed by South and South-West Asia (figure 7). While the frequency of disasters and total economic damage is lower in the Pacific (figure 8), its economies and people are acutely vulnerable to disasters, especially when considering the number of deaths as a share of the population.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "0c0a8565-aef6-4422-b0c3-f8153cbefadc": {"__data__": {"id_": "0c0a8565-aef6-4422-b0c3-f8153cbefadc", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/delivering-sustainable-development-goals-through-solutions-energy-food-and-finance-nexus-2023-asia-pacific-sdg-partnership", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Delivering on the Sustainable Development Goals through Solutions at the Energy, Food and Finance Nexus: 2023 Asia-Pacific SDG Partnership Rep