ure 18). Following the pandemic, the debt dynamic, both public and private, has worsened. Rising interest rates and borrowing costs and currency depreciation have increased the current cost of servicing debt, while slower growth, ongoing fiscal subsidies and other stimuli to address food and energy crisis weigh on countries\u2019", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "8706c688-ae05-43dd-bd9b-d1c016224303": {"__data__": {"id_": "8706c688-ae05-43dd-bd9b-d1c016224303", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/delivering-sustainable-development-goals-through-solutions-energy-food-and-finance-nexus-2023-asia-pacific-sdg-partnership", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Delivering on the Sustainable Development Goals through Solutions at the Energy, Food and Finance Nexus: 2023 Asia-Pacific SDG Partnership Report", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/delivering-sustainable-development-goals-through-solutions-energy-food-and-finance-nexus-2023-asia-pacific-sdg-partnership", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "61c289dbb54294b26394cace3113f3b1bfc014dfc15e774857b00a02bc1cb69d"}, "3": {"node_id": "a5690611-d54f-4f7c-a72d-d7a7d749ff6d", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/delivering-sustainable-development-goals-through-solutions-energy-food-and-finance-nexus-2023-asia-pacific-sdg-partnership", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programm